Former Bosasa COO, Angelo Agrizzi, has been moved to a private hospital. Sally Burdett talks to his lawyer Daniel Witz. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former Bosasa COO, Angelo Agrizzi, has been moved to an undisclosed private hospital. Agrizzi is said to be on a ventilator in the intensive care unit. READ: Angelo Agrizzi moved from prison to hospital Agrizzi was admitted to a government hospital on Thursday, after spending one night in prison. eNCA understands that his family and doctor requested the move. READ: Angelo Agrizzi tests negative for COVID-19 They’re concerned that his health is deteriorating.
 
Agrizzi faces corruption and fraud charges. He failed in his bid to secure bail last Wednesday. Watch the full interview with Angelo Agrizzi's lawyer Daniel Witz in the video above.